docker-compose up -d
docker ps ##show containers


start postgres docker
docker exec -it ai_postgres psql -U admin -d analytics_db
Once started you will see "analytics_db=# ". This is postgres running.

List all running containers with their names:
docker ps
This command displays a table with various columns including CONTAINER ID, IMAGE, STATUS, and NAMES.

List all containers (running and stopped) with their names:
docker ps -a
The -a (or --all) flag ensures that all containers are listed, not just the running ones.

List only the names of all containers:
docker ps -a --format "{{.Names}}"


\conninfo ##connection info --> You are connected to database "analytics_db" as user "admin" via socket in "/var/run/postgresql" at port "5432".
\dt ##list tables 
SELECT * FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES;
SHOW search_path; ##which schema I am in -->  "$user", public
\q ## quit

Python
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install pandas numpy psycopg2-binary
pip install sqlalchemy
python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip --> new version was avialable

mkdir data
touch data/generate_data.py

run python data/generate_data.py
pip freeze > requirements.txt

##LOAD DATE TO DOCKER
docker cp data/users.csv ai_postgres:/users.csv
docker cp data/athletes.csv ai_postgres:/athletes.csv
docker cp data/tokens.csv ai_postgres:/tokens.csv
docker cp data/trades.csv ai_postgres:/trades.csv
docker cp data/events.csv ai_postgres:/events.csv

Create query_runner.py
Run: python app/db/query_runner.py

Run: python -m app.main ## to see app (the folder) as a package - imports stuff from app folder




